parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the brake pedal is depressed
the vehicle feels like it's going to lurch forward
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the moon roof/sunroof can cause injury to occupants from shattered glass, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: without any prior impact or damage
hollow-sounding pop. Occupants may be showered with glass fragments
and the explosion can occur at any time
including while driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the front suspension can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to other components.
symptoms: The front tires wear out prematurely
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle vibrates or shakes excessively
